description: Try our easy to follow Ten Minute Chicken Chow Mein recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Ten Minute Chicken Chow Mein Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1-450g Mr Chen's Chow Mein Noodles (from the freezer)

recipeInstructions.text: Cook chow mein noodle stir-fry according to pack instructions, in microwave 6 – 7 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a bowl combine chicken with soy & oyster sauces, Chinese cooking wine (if using) and honey, and toss to coat.

Heat the peanut oil in a large frying pan or wok over medium heat. Add chicken and baby corn to pan and sear, tossing regularly for approximately 4-5 minutes, or until cooked to your liking. Remove pan from heat and keep warm.
Once noodles are ready, return pan to the heat, and combine chicken and corn with the noodles, bean sprouts and sesame oil. Cook whilst tossing for 1 – 2 minutes.
Divide stir-fry between serving bowls, and serve topped with spring onions and toasted sesame seeds.
